-- Gold Rises Toward $1,400 After Reports Russia Detects Missiles
-- B y   N i c h o l a s   L a r k i n
-- 2013-09-03T09:13:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-03/gold-rises-toward-1-400-after-reports-russia-detects-missiles.html
Gold rebdouned in  London , climbing
toward $1,400 an ounce, after Interfax reported that Russia
detected a missile launch.  Missiles appear to be headed toward eastern Mediterranean,
RIA Novosti reported, citing comments Russian Defense Minister
Sergei Shoigu made to President Vladimir Putin. Some investors
buy gold as a store of value.  Gold for immediate delivery added 0.2 percent to $1,394.56
an ounce by 10:10 a.m. in London. Prices dropped as much as 0.5
percent earlier today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nicholas Larkin at 
 nlarkin1@bloomberg.net  